				<div class="post clearfix">
					<h1 class="title">Sorbetto di Melagrana {Pomegranate Sorbet}</h1>
											<p class="post-meta">Posted  by <a href="http://www.bellalimento.com/author/paula/" title="Posts by Paula" rel="author">Paula</a> in <a href="http://www.bellalimento.com/category/recipes/" title="View all posts in All Recipes" rel="category tag">All Recipes</a>, <a href="http://www.bellalimento.com/category/recipes/desserts/" title="View all posts in Desserts" rel="category tag">Desserts</a>, <a href="http://www.bellalimento.com/category/vegetarian/" title="View all posts in Vegetarian" rel="category tag">Vegetarian</a> | <a href="http://www.bellalimento.com/2011/05/30/sorbetto-di-melagrana-pomegranate-sorbet/#comments" title="Comment on Sorbetto di Melagrana {Pomegranate Sorbet}">24 comments</a></p>
																				
								
					<div class="pin-it-btn-wrapper"><a href="http://pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.bellalimento.com%2F2011%2F05%2F30%2Fsorbetto-di-melagrana-pomegranate-sorbet%2F&media=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.bellalimento.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2011%2F05%2FPomegranate-Sorbet-012-533x800.jpg&description=Sorbetto+di+Melagrana+%7BPomegranate+Sorbet%7D" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push(['_trackEvent','outbound-article','http://pinterest.com']);" count-layout="horizontal" class="pin-it-button2"><img border="0" style="border:0;" src="//assets.pinterest.com/images/PinExt.png" title="Pin It" /></a></div><p><span class="rdetector_placeholder_before"></span></p>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-9028" title="Pomegranate Sorbet" src="http://www.bellalimento.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/Pomegranate-Sorbet-012-533x800.jpg" alt="" width="533" height="800" /></p>
<p>I&#8217;ve officially brought my ice cream maker out of it&#8217;s winter hibernation. It gets a pretty heavy workout in our house during the warm months and needs a little reprieve during the colder months ; ) The only decision what was to make in it first. A refreshing sorbet seemed like a great choice ; ) <span id="more-9024"></span></p>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-9030" title="Pomegranate Sorbet" src="http://www.bellalimento.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/Pomegranate-Sorbet-001-533x800.jpg" alt="" width="533" height="800" /></p>
<p>I&#8217;m fortunate to work with many amazing companies. POM Wonderful is one of those companies. We adore <a href="http://www.pomwonderful.com" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push(['_trackEvent','outbound-article','http://www.pomwonderful.com']);" target="_blank">POM Wonderful</a> pomegranate juice in our house, and always have at least one double bubble bottle {try saying that three times fast} in our fridge&#8230;so yes, a pomegranate sorbet was the natural choice! You&#8217;ll hardly believe that there are just THREE simple ingredients in this refreshing sorbet and it comes together in a snap.</p>
<p>You can always find a bottle of POM Wonderful juice in the market so you can whip up this sorbet anytime your heart desires. I think it would even be fantastic using the POM cherry or POM blueberry juices as well!</p>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-9031" title="Pomegranate Sorbet" src="http://www.bellalimento.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/Pomegranate-Sorbet-004-533x800.jpg" alt="" width="533" height="800" /></p>
<p>Once you&#8217;ve made our Pomegranate Sorbet you can also try ourÂ  <a href="http://www.bellalimento.com/2010/06/25/gelato-al-melograno-pomegranate-gelato/" >Pomegranate Gelato</a>.</p>
<p>Baci!</p>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-6221" title="signature2010" src="http://www.bellalimento.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/signature2010.png" alt="" width="250" height="80" /></p>
<p><em>Disclaimer: POM Wonderful sponsored this post. My opinions however, are my own, always have been, always will be.</em></p>
<p><em><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-9035" title="pom-wonderful-logo" src="http://www.bellalimento.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/pom-wonderful-logo.jpg" alt="" width="144" height="68" /><br />
</em></p>
<p><em> </em></p>
<p><em> </em></p>
<p><em>You can connect with POM Wonderful on<a href="http://www.twitter.com/POMWonderful" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push(['_trackEvent','outbound-article','http://www.twitter.com']);" target="_blank"> TWITTER</a> and <a href="http://www.facebook.com/#!/pomwonderful" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push(['_trackEvent','outbound-article','http://www.facebook.com']);" target="_blank">FACEBOOK</a>.<br />
</em></p>
<p><br />
<a href="http://www.bellalimento.com/2011/05/30/sorbetto-di-melagrana-pomegranate-sorbet/print/"  title="Print This Recipe" rel="nofollow"><img class="WP-PrintIcon" src="http://www.bellalimento.com/wp-content/plugins/wp-print/images/print.gif" alt="Print This Recipe" title="Print This Recipe" style="border: 0px;" /></a></p>
<p><em>Sorbetto di Melagrana {Pomegranate Sorbet}</em><br />
<span style="text-decoration: underline;">What you&#8217;ll need: </span><br />
3/4 cup sugar<br />
1 cup water<br />
16 ounces POM Wonderful Pomegranate Juice<br />
fresh mint leaves &#8211; optional to garnish</p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;">What to do:</span><br />
1. Into a deep sided pan add: sugar and water. Cook over medium &#8211; high heat until sugar is dissolved. Stirring as necessary. Add pomegranate juice and continue cooking.</p>
<p>2. Remove pan from heat and allow it to come to room temperature. Once cool, place pan into refrigerator and allow to cool completely.</p>
<p>3. Place pomegranate mixture into your ice cream maker and mix according to machine directions.</p>
<p>4. Serve immediately. Freeze any uneaten portions.</p>
<p>Buon Appetito!
<p><a id="magellan"></a><br />
